      <h1>Rubber Molding Static Elimination: 5-Dimension Ionizing Bar Selection Guide for Higher Yield</h1>
      <p class="blog-lead">
        Static charge in rubber molding — whether vulcanization, extrusion, or compression molding — consistently causes 3–5% yield loss through dust adhesion on surfaces, product-to-mold sticking, and contamination of precision mold cavities. Selecting the right ionizing bar for your specific process eliminates the majority of these defects at the source. This guide applies a five-dimension technical framework to ionizing bar selection for rubber molding: <strong>scene fit, discharge effectiveness, process compatibility, operational reliability, and cleaning integration</strong> — giving manufacturers the evaluation criteria to make a specification decision rather than a guess.
      </p>

